http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/Campus-recruitment-a-big-hit/article13993186.ece

The Birla Institute of Technology (BIT) in Mesra has attracted 74 recruiters for the campus recruitment programme in 2015-16. Announcing this here, Vice-Chancellor Manoj Kumar Mishra said it had generated 1,135 offers.Addressing the Diamond Jubilee celebration and the 26th Convocation of BIT in the presence of President Pranab Mukherjee, Prof. Mishra said the offers came in the fields of retail, e-commerce, consulting, infrastructure, telecom, automobile, heavy engineering, IT services and others.“The average salary is Rs 7.7 lakh per annum and the highest compensation is Rs 26.83 lakh offered by a company,” he added. -- PTI